2026-04-25T14:03:40.166Z JOY-0115-8B comment.added "Plan: (1) FilterSpec.members becomes a MemberFilter enum (Any/Specific(Vec<String>)/Unassigned/AnyAssigned). (2) FilterArgs surface change: --mine becomes long-only; -M is rebound to milestone (BREAKING from previous --mine binding); -m/--members <SPEC> is added with comma-separated values. (3) Special tokens parsed in FilterArgs::to_spec(root): 'me' resolves via identity::resolve_identity + that human's ai_delegations keys; 'none'/'unassigned' map to MemberFilter::Unassigned; '*' to AnyAssigned; mixing 'none'/'*' with other tokens errors. (4) ExtraColumns::from_args accepts 'members' as an alias for 'assignee'. (5) Unit tests in joy-core/filter.rs for each enum variant and the assignee-aliasing. (6) Manual integration check: -m horst.schwarz@joydev.com, -m me, -m none, -m '*', --mine, -M JOY-MS-01. (7) Note: AI delegation expansion only kicks in when 'me' resolves to a human; AI sessions resolve to their own AI member ID directly so -m me from an AI session matches that AI's items only." [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
